name: Lopez
overview: Exploring the real George Lopez we rarely get to see, pushed and pulled between the worlds of race, class and fame, yet always having a hard time fitting in.

episodes.name: Slave for a Day
episodes.overview: George gets auctioned off at his daughter's elite private school fundraiser attended by his enemies. He doesn't want to embarrass himself or his daughter, or get bought by Snoop Dogg.

episodes.name: George Takes a Hike
episodes.overview: George goes on a date with a dog rescue volunteer after adopting a rescue dog.

episodes.name: Down and Drought in Beverly Hills
episodes.overview: George gets in a twitter war with an angry groupie and faces a tough choice between the lawn he loves and a chance to build his brand.

episodes.name: George's Party
episodes.overview: George throws a neighborhood party at the urging of his new girlfriend.

episodes.name: Land of the Rings
episodes.overview: George returns to his roots and offers championship rings to a local baseball team and thinks about buying land in his old neighborhood.

episodes.name: George Hosts a Golf Tournament
episodes.overview: George hosts a celebrity golf tournament to strengthen his Vegas residency credentials while his daughter goes AWOL.

episodes.name: My $uper $weet $ixteen
episodes.overview: George plans a big birthday party for his daughter, but schedules it for the same day of another party hosted by a wealthy family.

episodes.name: George Doubles Down
episodes.overview: George considers a new opening act after learning that Maronzio has other career goals.

episodes.name: George Gets Roasted
episodes.overview: George agrees to be roasted, but his wife interferes and legally ties up his jokes, leaving George without an act.

episodes.name: George Needs Vegas
episodes.overview: George becomes frustrated with community troubles at his Las Vegas and San Fernando properties.

episodes.name: Fear and Loving on the Way to Las Vegas
episodes.overview:
George is stranded in the desert after his car breaks down and gets help from a mysterious couple.
Watch Soon

episodes.name: George Goes All In
episodes.overview: George fires everyone and pushes one last time for his Vegas residency show, but as things go out of control he begins to have second thoughts.

episodes.name: Leaving Las Vegas
episodes.overview: George quits his Las Vegas residency, causing big problems. Manolo gets out of jail and introduces his roommate, Hector, to everyone.

episodes.name: Moving on and Moving in
episodes.overview: George and Olly pitch his new show idea to the network. Manolo is nervous about starting school to get his GED and Hector nearly destroys a bakery.

episodes.name: Coco for Lopez
episodes.overview: George has to navigate political correctness in order to convince a transgender actress to co-star in “Valleys.” Meanwhile, Manolo has problems with bullies at school and Maronzio starts a podcast.

episodes.name: George Dates His Daughter
episodes.overview: George is asked out on a date by a beautiful woman: the actress who played his daughter on his old TV show, "Masiela Lusha" as Carmen, Olly starts tutoring Manolo.

episodes.name: No Country Club for Young Men
episodes.overview: George gets Hector a job at his country club, but he falls in with a bad crowd of rich kids; Olly's little sister rolls back into town; Manolo struggles to stay focused in his GED class

episodes.name: George Breaks In
episodes.overview: George appears on a home shopping channel to sell his grill and meets Lori, a billionairess. Manolo gets glasses.

episodes.name: George Gets Schooled
episodes.overview: George and Lori continue seeing each other while his gig as a guest lecturer at a local university goes badly; Manolo starts seeing his teacher after hours; Olly's sister's dating life becomes intertwined with Olly's work.

episodes.name: George Clowns Around
episodes.overview: After alienating some of his core Latino fans, George appears as a guest on Platanito, a Latino talk show hosted by a clown; Hector makes his solo debut on the home shopping channel; Manolo and his teacher heat up.

episodes.name: Cuck You George Lopez
episodes.overview: George's friends have him worried that Lori wears the pants in their relationship. Pfeiffer complicates Olly's work life. Manolo gets laser eye surgery to please Wendy.

episodes.name: Lost in Trans-lation
episodes.overview: George's co-star's wild behavior puts the future of his TV show in jeopardy. Maronzio tries to woo his ex. Hector has a problem selling at work, which gets George and Lori talking again.
